text.section:
The Corporation may invest any of its funds in:
Cash or deposits in checking or savings accounts with or certificates of deposit of:
Any bank that is a member of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation; and
Any savings and loan association whose deposits are insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation;
Cash or deposits in share or deposit accounts with or certificates of deposit or notes of any credit union that is a member of the Corporation, the National Credit Union Administration Share Insurance Program, or a similar insurance program;
Obligations of:
The United States or any state or any political subdivision of any state;
Any commission, instrumentality, agency, or authority of the United States or any state; and
Any corporation that is incorporated under the laws of the United States or of any state;
Readily marketable, dividend-paying shares of any corporation that is incorporated under the laws of the United States or of any state, except that it may not invest more than 10 percent of its total assets in these shares nor more than 3 percent of its total assets in the shares of any one corporation; and
Any other investments, including common trust investments, that are permitted by law or authorized by the Commissioner for credit unions.
